main event: A civilian observed an unidentified flying object for over 2 hours in Trenton, Ohio, on August 17, 1965.
interesting points: The observation lasted more than 2 hours and the object remained stationary., The exact shape of the object is redacted in the report., There was both physical evidence and some photographs referenced., The observer described the object as making a loud sound and changing colors between orange, amber, green, and blue., The observer provided a sketch indicating the object was boomerang-shaped.
